The paper deals with online allocation problems in the context of online advertising, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new stochastic model that captures the nature of traffic spikes, which is a problem related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper provides provable bounds for the proposed algorithms, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT).
